1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO CREATE A TIMESHARE TRUSTEE FORECLOSURE PROCESS FOR
3 CERTAIN DELINQUENT ASSESSMENTS FOR TIMESHARES LOCATED IN THIS
4 STATE AND TO CHANGE THE PROCESS FOR ESTABLISHING PATERNITY OF
5 CHILDREN BORN OUT OF WEDLOCK.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. G.S. 93A-62 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 93A-62. Delinquent assessments; developer guarantee.
9 (a) Delinquent assessments may bear interest at the highest rate permitted by law or at
10 some lesser rate established by the managing entity. In addition to interest, the managing entity
11 may charge a reasonable administrative late fee for each delinquent assessment. Any costs of
12 collection, including reasonable collection agency fees and reasonable attorney's fees, incurred
13 in the collection of a delinquent assessment shall be paid by the owner and shall be secured by a
14 lien in favor of the managing entity upon the timeshare with respect to which the delinquent
15 assessment has been incurred.
16 (b) The managing entity may deny the use of the timeshare units or facilities, including
17 the denial of the right to make a reservation or the cancellation of a confirmed reservation for
18 timeshare periods, to any owner who is delinquent in the payment of any assessments made by
19 the managing entity against the owner for common expenses, in accordance with the following:
20 (1) The managing entity must, no less than 30 days after the date the assessment
21 is due, notify the owner in writing of the total amount of any delinquency
22 which then exists, including any accrued interest and late charges permitted
23 to be imposed under the terms of the timeshare program or by law and
24 including a per diem amount. The notice shall be sent to the owner at the
25 owner's known address as recorded in the books and records of the timeshare
26 program.
27 (2) The notice shall clearly state that the owner will not be permitted to use the
28 owner's timeshare, that the owner will not be permitted to make a reservation
29 in the timeshare program's reservation system, or that any confirmed
30 reservation may be canceled until the total amount of such delinquency is
31 satisfied in full or until the owner produces satisfactory evidence that the
32 delinquency does not exist.
33 (3) The notice shall be effective to bar the use of the owner and those claiming
34 use rights under the owner, including the owner's guests, lessees, and persons
