1 receiving use rights in the timeshare through an exchange program; provided,
2 however, that (i) a managing entity desiring to deny the use of the timeshare
3 to persons receiving use rights in the delinquent owner's timeshare through an
4 exchange program that has an affiliation agreement with the managing entity
5 shall notify the affiliated exchange company in writing of the denial of use at
6 the time that the notice was sent to the owner and (ii) any person claiming
7 through the affiliated exchange program who has received a confirmed
8 assignment of the delinquent owner's use rights from the affiliated exchange
9 company prior to the expiration of 48 hours after the receipt by the affiliated
10 exchange company of the written notice from the managing entity shall be
11 permitted by the managing entity to use the owner's use rights.
12 (4) Any costs reasonably incurred by the managing entity in connection with its
13 compliance with the requirements of this section may be assessed by the
14 managing entity against the delinquent owner and collected in the same
15 manner as if those costs were common expenses of the timeshare program
16 allocable solely to the delinquent purchaser.
17 (5) A managing entity may not enforce the denial of use against any one owner
18 or group of owners without similarly enforcing it against all owners, including
19 all developers.
20 (c) In addition to the denial of use pursuant to subsection (b) of this section, the managing
21 entity may give further notice to the delinquent owner that the managing entity may rent the
22 delinquent owner's timeshare, or any use rights appurtenant thereto, in accordance with the
23 following:
24 (1) A further notice of intent to rent must be given no less than 30 days after the
25 date the assessment is due and must be delivered to the purchaser in the
26 manner required for notices under subsection (b) of this section.
27 (2) The notice shall state that unless the owner satisfies the delinquency in full, or
28 unless the owner produces satisfactory evidence that the delinquency does not
29 exist, the purchaser will be bound by the terms of any rental contract entered
30 into by the managing entity with respect to the owner's timeshare or
31 appurtenant use rights.
32 (3) The notice shall state that the owner will remain liable for any difference
33 between the amount of the delinquency and the net amount produced by the
34 rental contract and applied against the delinquency, and the managing entity
35 shall not be required to provide any further notice to the owner regarding any
36 residual delinquency.
37 (4) The managing entity's efforts to secure a rental shall not commence on a date
38 earlier than 10 days after the date of the notice of intent to rent.
39 (5) The managing entity must apply the proceeds of any rental, net of any rental
40 commissions, cleaning charges, travel agent commissions, or any other
41 commercially reasonable charges reasonably and usually incurred by the
42 managing entity in securing rentals to the delinquent owner's account.
43 (6) A managing entity may make a reasonable determination regarding the
44 priority of rentals of timeshares and, if the delinquent owner whose timeshare
45 is rented cannot be specifically determined due to the structure of the
46 timeshare program, the managing entity may allocate any net rental proceeds
47 in any reasonable manner.
48 (7) In securing a rental, the managing entity shall not be required to obtain the
49 highest nightly rental rate available, nor any particular rental rate, and the
50 managing entity shall not be required to rent the entire timeshare or
51 appurtenant rights; however, the managing entity must use reasonable efforts
