38 has occurred. The certificate shall include the time, location, and date of the
39 sale, that the timeshare was sold, the amounts secured by the lien, and the
40 amount of the highest bid. A copy of the certificate shall be mailed by
41 first-class mail to the owner's address as recorded in the books and records of
42 the timeshare program. Upon issuance of a certificate of sale, all rights of
43 redemption are foreclosed and shall terminate.
44 (m) A sale conducted under this section releases the owner from liability for all amounts
45 secured by the lien. The managing entity or holder of the lien have no right to a deficiency
46 judgment against the owner after a sale of the owner's timeshare under this section.
47 (n) Within 10 calendar days after the trustee conducts a sale under this section, the trustee
48 shall execute and file with the clerk of superior court, a certificate of compliance that has been
