33 (q) The certificate of compliance and the trustee's deed together are presumptive evidence
34 of the truth of the matters set forth in them, and action to set aside the sale and void the trustee's
35 deed may not be filed or otherwise pursued against any person acquiring the timeshare interest
36 for value. The issuance and recording of the trustee's deed is presumed valid and may be relied
37 upon by third parties without actual knowledge of irregularities in the foreclosure proceedings.
38 If for any reason there is an irregularity in the foreclosure proceedings, a purchaser becomes
39 subrogated to all the rights of the lienholder to the indebtedness that it secured to the extent
40 necessary to re-foreclose the assessment lien in order to correct the irregularity and becomes
41 entitled to an action de novo for foreclosure of such assessment lien. Any subsequent
42 re-foreclosure required to correct an irregularity may be conducted under G.S. 93A-62.1.
43 (r) The managing entity, holder of the lien, or designated trustee may combine the claim
